Source: Associated Press, 1 Nov 2000 - 02:07 AM [edited
<http://ap.tbo.com/ap/breaking/MGA79R9O0FC.html>

Mosquito-Borne Dengue Kills at Least Six People in Honduras
-----------------------------------------------------------
TEGUCIGALPA: A fatal form of mosquito-borne dengue fever [dengue
hemorrhagic fever? has killed at least 6 people in the past month and
filled the Honduran Government's 18 hospitals to capacity, officials said.
Another 130 people were being treated for dengue fever on Tue 31 Oct 2000
and 381 others were under observation. [An additional? 2 children died
over the weekend, and the majority of the victims have been under the age
of 12.
Dengue is a painful disease characterized by headaches, rashes, cramps and
severe back and muscle pains. The variety that is striking Honduras causes
internal bleeding [dengue hemorrhagic fever and can be fatal. So far this
year, Honduras has counted 6 478 cases [of dengue fever compared to 11 000
last year.
